NOTION.name: Notion
NOTION.tagline: Unifying notes, docs, wikis, projects, and databases into a single connected workspace
NOTION.overview: Notion is an all-in-one workspace platform founded in 2013 by Ivan Zhao and Simon Last. The company provides a connected workspace combining notes, docs, databases, wikis, and project management. Notion reached $10B valuation in 2021 after raising $275M Series D. The company hit $500M ARR in 2025 with 100M users worldwide—a 5x growth from 20M in 2022. Over 50% of Fortune 500 companies use Notion. Recent AI features, Notion Calendar, Forms, and advanced Automation have driven enterprise adoption. Acquisitions include Automate.io (2021), Cron (2022), and Skiff (2024).

NETLIFY.name: Netlify
NETLIFY.tagline: Pioneering composable web development by connecting frameworks, content, and modern workflows
NETLIFY.overview: Netlify is a web development platform founded in 2015 by Matt Biilmann who coined the term 'Jamstack'. The company raised $105M at $2B valuation in November 2021. Revenue reached $46.3M in 2024, up from $33M in 2023. Netlify celebrated 10 years since launch in February 2025. The platform competes with Vercel, Cloudflare Pages, and AWS Amplify. Investors include a16z, Kleiner Perkins, Menlo Ventures, and founders from GitHub, Heroku, Slack, and Figma.

products.name: Netlify Platform
products.description: Deploy and host modern web projects

N26.name: N26
N26.tagline: Europe's leading mobile bank with €440M revenue—first profitable quarter in 2024 after BaFin cap lifted
N26.overview: N26 is a German direct bank founded in 2013 by Valentin Stalf and Maximilian Tayenthal. The company offers mobile banking services across 24 European markets. In Q3 2024, N26 achieved its first-ever quarterly profit (€2.8M net operating income) after BaFin lifted its customer growth restriction in June 2024. Revenue grew 40% to €440M in 2024, with deposits exceeding €10B for the first time. Customer sign-ups more than doubled to 200K/month. N26 plans to launch business banking and expand investment products in 2025.

products.name: N26 Standard
products.description: Free mobile bank account with Mastercard

NEON.name: Neon
NEON.tagline: Providing serverless Postgres with instant branching, autoscaling, and scale-to-zero capabilities
NEON.overview: Neon is a serverless PostgreSQL database platform founded in 2021 by Nikita Shamgunov (ex-SingleStore CEO), Heikki Linnakangas, and Stas Kelvich. The company raised $130M total including $25M from Microsoft's M12 in August 2024. In May 2025, Databricks announced acquisition of Neon for approximately $1B. Neon's serverless architecture features autoscaling and scale-to-zero capabilities. Key investors include M12, General Catalyst, Menlo Ventures, Databricks Ventures, and Founders Fund.

NAVAN.name: Navan
NAVAN.tagline: All-in-one corporate travel and expense management platform simplifying business travel
NAVAN.overview: Navan (formerly TripActions) is a corporate travel and expense management platform founded in May 2015 by Ariel Cohen and Ilan Twig in Palo Alto, California. The company provides an integrated solution that combines travel booking, corporate payment cards, expense automation, and real-time analytics. Navan serves over 10,000 customers worldwide including Zoom, Lyft, Unilever, Adobe, Shopify, and Christie's. As of October 2025, Navan is preparing for an IPO on Nasdaq under ticker "NAVN", targeting a valuation of $6.45 billion with plans to raise up to $960 million. The company reported trailing twelve-month revenue of $613 million (up 32% YoY) and gross booking volume of $7.6 billion (up 34% YoY) as of July 2025. Navan's AI assistant Ava resolves over 50% of user interactions, and its Navan Connect technology enables automated expense management across 250+ banks without requiring companies to switch card providers.

NETSKOPE.name: Netskope
NETSKOPE.tagline: Cloud security leader delivering SASE and zero trust solutions for the AI era
NETSKOPE.overview: Netskope is a global SASE leader founded in 2012 that helps organizations apply zero trust principles to protect data and defend against cyber threats. The company went public on September 18, 2025, achieving an $8.6 billion market cap on its first trading day. With its flagship Netskope One platform, the company serves over 4,300 customers across 90 countries, including 30+ Fortune 100 companies. Netskope has been recognized as a Leader in Gartner Magic Quadrant for both SASE Platforms and Security Service Edge since their inception.

NEURALINK.name: Neuralink
NEURALINK.tagline: Developing brain-computer interfaces to restore autonomy for people with paralysis and unlock human potential
NEURALINK.overview: Neuralink is a neurotechnology company founded by Elon Musk in 2016 to develop implantable brain-computer interfaces (BCIs). The company's flagship device, the N1 chip, is a coin-sized implant that can read neural signals to enable people with paralysis to control computers and phones with their thoughts. In January 2024, Neuralink implanted its first human patient, Noland Arbaugh, who demonstrated the ability to play chess and video games using only his mind. The company received FDA approval for human trials in 2023 and has since expanded trials. Neuralink raised $680M+ at a valuation of $8.5 billion, with backing from Founders Fund, Google Ventures, and other investors.

NURO.name: Nuro
NURO.tagline: AI-first autonomy company building the most scalable self-driving technology
NURO.overview: Nuro is an American robotics company founded in 2016 by former Google/Waymo engineers Jiajun Zhu and Dave Ferguson. Originally focused on autonomous delivery vehicles, Nuro has pivoted to licensing its advanced Level 4 self-driving technology, the Nuro Driver™, to OEMs and mobility platforms. The company has achieved over 1.4 million autonomous miles with zero at-fault incidents across five years of driverless deployments. In 2025, Nuro partnered with Uber and Lucid to deploy 20,000+ robotaxis globally, marking a major shift from delivery to passenger transport. As of August 2025, the company has raised $2.34 billion and achieved a $6 billion valuation.

highlights.text: Achieved 1.4M+ autonomous miles with zero at-fault incidents.
First company to receive NHTSA autonomous exemption.
California DMV granted first-ever AV deployment permit to Nuro.
